body:
canvas.DrawRect doesn't appear to be working consistently with SKGLView. I am drawing a bunch of rectangles in a loop and everything works great using rectangles with a regular SKCanvasView. Also, interestingly enough, DrawRoundRect works as a substitute with GLView as long as the rounding radius provided is greater than 0.

                canvas.DrawRect(rect, paint); // Doesn't show in GL
                canvas.DrawRoundRect(rect, 1, 1, paint); // Shows in either
                canvas.DrawRoundRect(rect, 0, 0, paint); // Doesn't show in GL

I am using version 1.57.1 installed from Nuget. 


**=========== Current work around using SKPath ==============**
```

using (var path = new SKPath()) {
	path.FillType = SKPathFillType.EvenOdd;
	
	"loop each draw object"
	{
        	path.Reset();
        	path.AddRect(rect);
        	canvas.DrawPath(path, paint);
	}
}
```

_This leads me to believe there is suspect code within how DrawRect creates the underlying path, if that is how it does the drawing under the hood - haven't looked yet though._
